  <fr:p>Next we identify <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta _{J}]]></fr:tex> with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[1_{J}]]></fr:tex>. By incoherent naturality, we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{J};s = \alpha _{I}]]></fr:tex>; thus by our splitting of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{I}]]></fr:tex> we have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _{J};s = r;s]]></fr:tex> and hence by postcomposing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[r]]></fr:tex> and canceling via <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\eta :s;r=1_{I}]]></fr:tex> we conclude that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\alpha _J = r]]></fr:tex>. Therefore <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\beta _J=s;\alpha _J=s;r=1_{J}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
